  "target_response": {
    "text": "Creatine sits in a completely different category from banned or prescription substances — it's legal, sold openly, and one of the most-studied supplements in sports science. It helps you squeeze out extra reps in short, hard efforts and supports muscle gain alongside training; it isn't a stimulant and it isn't a gateway to anything. The standard approach is 3 to 5 g of creatine monohydrate daily, with no loading phase needed. Expect roughly 1 kg of early water weight — that's muscle cells holding water, not fat. Two sensible caveats: pick a third-party-tested product, since supplements are loosely regulated, and clear it with your doctor first if you have any kidney condition. Otherwise, for someone training strength consistently like you are, it's a reasonable and boring choice — in the good sense.",
